  New version

*mosfet-liquid-widgets-0.9.6_pre2 (24 Jan 2002)

  24 Jan 2002; Bart Verwilst <verwilst@gentoo.org> ChangeLog  :
  New version

*mosfet-liquid-widgets-0.9.6_pre1 (01 Nov 2002)

  01 Nov 2002; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> ChangeLog  :

  A new version that requires kde 3.1.x and qt 3.1. Therefore it is masked.

*mosfet-liquid-widgets-0.9.5-r1 (24 Aug 2002)

  18 Mar 2003; Jason Wever <weeve@gentoo.org>
  mosfet-liquid-widgets-0.9.5-r1.ebuild:
  Added sparc to keywords.

  24 Aug 2002; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> ChangeLog  :

  Install the ksplash images (the ones you see while KDE is loading) into
  the kdelibs dir, not into the prefix. Otherwise they do not work.

Relocated to x11-themes

*mosfet-liquid-widgets-0.9.5 (14 April 2002)

  15 Jul 2002; Mark Guertin <gerk@gentoo.org>
  Added ppc to keywords

  14 April 2002; Bart Verwilst <verwilst@gentoo.org> ChangeLog :

  New release, fixes some more bugs.. Removed older 0.9.x ebuilds.
  0.7 still available for KDE 2 users.

*mosfet-liquid-widgets-0.9.4 (14 April 2002)

  14 April 2002; Bart Verwilst <verwilst@gentoo.org> ChangeLog :

  New release, fixes some more bugs.. And also removed the older 0.9.3 
  ebuild.


*mosfet-liquid-widgets-0.9.3 (12 April 2002)

  12 April 2002; Bart Verwilst <verwilst@gentoo.org> ChangeLog :

  New release, fixes some more bugs..Removed the older 0.9.2 ebuild. I'm 
  still keeping 0.7-r3 for our KDE 2 users.

*mosfet-liquid-widgets-0.9.1 (24 March 2002)

  24 March 2002; Bart Verwilst <verwilst@gentoo.org> ChangeLog :

  Added new KDE 3 mosfet liquid. The author says it's better than mosfet's
  Liquid has ever been. Also removed the oldest 0.7 revision. I'm keeping 
  0.7-r3 for our KDE 2 users.

*mosfet-liquid-widgets-0.7-r3 (1 Feb 2002)

  1 Feb 2002; G.Bevin <gbevin@gentoo.org> ChangeLog :
  
  Added initial ChangeLog which should be updated whenever the package is
  updated in any way. This changelog is targetted to users. This means that the
  comments should well explained and written in clean English. The details about
  writing correct changelogs are explained in the skel.ChangeLog file which you
  can find in the root directory of the portage repository.
